Write a C program to construct two binary trees from level-order input (using -1 to represent NULL) and check if both trees are identical. Two binary trees are considered identical if they are structurally the same and have the same node values.


Constraints:
1≤N≤100 — total number of input elements (including -1s for NULLs)

Node values range from −10^4-10^4.


Example:
Sample Input-1:

7
1 2 3 -1 -1 -1 -1
7
1 2 3 -1 -1 -1 -1

Sample Output-1:

Yes

Sample Input-2:

3
1 -1 2
3
1 2 -1

Sample Output-2:

No


Explanation:
Trees are constructed from the level-order traversal, interpreting -1 as a null node.

Recursively compare both trees:

Check root values

Recursively check left and right subtrees


